Generic single-database configuration for Alembic with SQLModel support.

This configuration is set up for Neon Serverless PostgreSQL with async support.

Usage:
------

1. Ensure DATABASE_URL environment variable is set in .env file
2. Import all SQLModel models in alembic/env.py (see comments in file)
3. Generate migration: `uv run alembic revision --autogenerate -m "description"`
4. Review generated migration in alembic/versions/
5. Apply migration: `uv run alembic upgrade head`
6. Rollback if needed: `uv run alembic downgrade -1`

Important Notes:
----------------

- Always review autogenerated migrations before applying
- Alembic autogenerate may miss certain changes (renames, complex constraints)
- Database URL is read from DATABASE_URL environment variable (not alembic.ini)
- Migrations use asyncpg for async PostgreSQL operations
- Target metadata is SQLModel.metadata (all models must be imported in env.py)

Commands:
---------

# Check current migration status
uv run alembic current

# Show migration history
uv run alembic history

# Generate new migration
uv run alembic revision --autogenerate -m "Add new field"

# Apply all pending migrations
uv run alembic upgrade head

# Rollback one migration
uv run alembic downgrade -1

# Rollback to specific version
uv run alembic downgrade <revision_id>

# Show SQL for migration without applying
uv run alembic upgrade head --sql

Configuration:
--------------

- script_location: alembic/ (this directory)
- file_template: %(rev)s_%(slug)s.py
- sqlalchemy.url: Read from DATABASE_URL environment variable
- target_metadata: SQLModel.metadata (from env.py)
